# System instructions for AI coding assistants working on AskTux

## Before starting any work
Read `.ai/project.ai` for the current project state — what's completed,
what's pending, architecture overview, and known issues.

## After completing a task
Update `.ai/project.ai`:
- Move items from [TBD] to [Completed] if they are fully done.
- Add any new [TBD] items that were discovered during the task.
- Update the description or architecture notes if the implementation
  changed the design.

## Code style
- C++17, GTK4 (gtkmm 4.0), Meson build.
- Header files use `#ifndef ASKTUX_..._H` (project-name prefix).
- Error messages printed to stderr with `[AskTux]` prefix.
- Debug/trace output goes through `Log::dbg()` (disabled unless --debug).
- RAII scoped timers via `ScopedTimer` (also gated by --debug).

## Key files at a glance
- `.ai/project.ai`      — full project state (read first)
- `data/schema.sql`     — database DDL + seed data (single source of truth)
- `src/Tool.h`          — tool registry (to be replaced by native function calling)
- `src/Config.h`        — SQLite-backed settings singleton
- `src/MainWindow.cpp`  — main UI logic, streaming, tool execution

## When in doubt
Ask the user for clarification rather than guessing intent.
This project is prerelease — breaking changes are expected and welcome.
